---
title: 3D Card Flip
description: A card that flips on hover using CSS 3D transforms and perspective.
slug: card-flip
cssFile: card-flip.css
explanation: The container sets <code>perspective</code> to create the 3D space. The inner element holds both faces and uses <code>transform-style:preserve-3d</code> so children exist in the same 3D plane. The back face is pre-rotated 180deg and both faces have <code>backface-visibility:hidden</code> so the correct face shows at each point of the flip.
---
{% extends "example.njk" %}
{% block demo %}
<div style="display:flex;gap:1.5rem;flex-wrap:wrap;justify-content:center">
	<div class="flip-card">
		<div class="flip-inner">
			<div class="flip-front">🎨 Front Side<br><small style="font-weight:400;opacity:.8">Hover to flip</small></div>
			<div class="flip-back">✨ Back Side<br><small style="font-weight:400;opacity:.8">Pure CSS</small></div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="flip-card">
		<div class="flip-inner">
			<div class="flip-front">Card Two<br><small style="font-weight:400;opacity:.8">Hover me</small></div>
			<div class="flip-back">No JS needed!</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
{% endblock %}

{% block html_code %}
{%- highlight "html" %}
<div class="flip-card">
  <div class="flip-inner">
    <div class="flip-front">Front</div>
    <div class="flip-back">Back</div>
  </div>
</div>
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}

{% block css_code %}
{%- highlight "css" %}
.flip-card {
  width: 200px;
  height: 130px;
  perspective: 800px;
}

.flip-inner {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  position: relative;
  transform-style: preserve-3d;
  transition: transform .55s ease;
}

.flip-card:hover .flip-inner {
  transform: rotateY(180deg);
}

.flip-front,
.flip-back {
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  border-radius: 12px;
  backface-visibility: hidden;
}

.flip-back {
  transform: rotateY(180deg);
}
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}
